# PyUIBuilder — Verified Rules

> All rules below are sourced directly from the PyUIBuilder GitHub source code
> (https://github.com/PaulleDemon/PyUIBuilder) and confirmed against real generated output.
> Do NOT guess — only use what is listed here.

---

## 1. Confirmed `widgetClass` values

These are the only widget types confirmed to exist in PyUIBuilder's source.
The value is the `static widgetType` property from each JS class.

| widgetClass      | Display name   | Qt equivalent     | Key extra attrs                          |
|------------------|----------------|-------------------|------------------------------------------|
| `main_window`    | Main Window    | QMainWindow       | `title`, `logo`, `menuData`, `menuHidden`, `resizable.x/y`, `maximized`, `initialPosition.*` |
| `frame`          | Frame          | QFrame / QWidget  | (base attrs only)                        |
| `label`          | Label          | QLabel            | `labelWidget` (text), `imageUpload`      |
| `button`         | Button         | QPushButton       | `buttonLabel` (text)                     |
| `entry`          | Entry          | QLineEdit         | `placeHolder`                            |
| `Text`           | Text           | QTextEdit         | (no extra attrs — note capital T)        |
| `option_menu`    | Option Menu    | QComboBox         | `defaultValue`, `widgetOptions: {inputs: [], selectedRadio: -1}` |
| `check_button`   | Check Box      | QCheckBox         | `checkLabel`, `defaultChecked` (bool)    |
| `radio_button`   | Radio Button   | QRadioButton      | `radios: {inputs: [], selectedRadio: -1}`|
| `scale`          | Scale/Slider   | QSlider           | `scale.min/max/step/default`, `orientation` |
| `spin_box`       | Spin Box       | QSpinBox          | `spinProps.min/max/step/default`         |
| `progressBar`    | Progress Bar   | QProgressBar      | `orientation`, `mode`, `styling.chunkColor` |

**NOT in the source (do not use):**
`tabWidget`, `listWidget`, `tableWidget`, `groupBox`, `comboBox` — these do not exist.
Use `frame` as a container placeholder for complex widgets.

